    <li><strong>Personal Fitness</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Outdoor Experiences</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Values-Based Education</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Creating a Safe and Welcoming Environment</strong></li>
</ul>
<section>
<h2 class="join">Why Join Troop 10?</h2>
</section>
<ol style="font-size: 17px;padding-right: 9cm;">
    <li><strong>Regular outdoor adventures: camping, hiking, canoeing, etc.</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Strong focus on leadership and character development.</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Supportive, trained adult volunteers.</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Opportunity to earn merit badges and the rank of Eagle Scout.</strong></li>
    <li><strong>Friendly, inclusive troop culture.</strong></li>

</ol>
<section>
<h2 class="meet-info">Meeting Information</h2>
</section>
<p style="font-size: 17px;padding-right: 9cm;">We meet on <em>Tuesdays </em>at 7:30 PM, at <strong>St. Benedict Church</strong> </p>
<a class="link"
          href="https://www.google.com/maps/dir/?api=1&destination=11045+Parsons+Rd,+Johns+Creek,+GA+30097,+USA"
